  "prompt": "With the terrorist attack in Uri, is going to war with Pakistan is the only option left with India ?",
  "response": "The situation between India and Pakistan, especially in the context of terrorist attacks such as the one in Uri, is complex and sensitive. While military responses are one option, they are not the only course of action available to India. \n\nDiplomatic efforts, international pressure, and intelligence cooperation are alternative approaches that can be considered. Historically, India has also engaged in various forms of dialogue with Pakistan, despite the challenges.\n\nIt's important to take into account the potential consequences of any military action, including escalation of conflict, civilian casualties, and long-term regional instability. Engaging the international community and exploring diplomatic channels are crucial steps in addressing such issues.\n\nUltimately, the decision on how to respond involves careful consideration of many factors, including security, regional stability, and international relations.",
